'''Roderick Alonso Miller Molina''' (born 3 April 1992) is a Panamanian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|centre-back]] for [[Azerbaijan Premier League]] club [[Turan Tovuz]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].<ref>[https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe257437/roderick-miller/ Profile at WorldFootball], worldfootball.net</ref>

==Club career==
In 2014, Miller had a spell in Mexican football with [[C.F. Mérida|Mérida]].<ref>[http://www.prensa.com/redaccion_de_prensa-com/Panameno-Miller-Merida-ascenso-mexicano_0_3997100268.html Panameño Miller entrena con el Mérida, en el fútbol de ascenso mexicano] - La Prensa {{in lang|es}}</ref>

On 21 January 2019, [[FC Okzhetpes]] announced the signing of Miller on a one-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=Официально: Родерик Миллер Молина игрок ФК Окжетпес |url=http://www.okzhetpes.kz/ru/news/oficialno-roderik-miller-molina-igrok-fk-okzhetpes |website=okzhetpes.kz/ |publisher=FC Okzhetpes |accessdate=21 January 2019 |language=Russian |date=21 January 2019}}</ref> Miller left Okzhetpes by mutual consent on 25 July 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=Родерик Миллер покидает Окжетпес» |url=http://www.okzhetpes.kz/ru/news/roderik-miller-pokidaet-okzhetpes |website=okzhetpes.kz/ |publisher=FC Okzhetpes |accessdate=28 July 2019 |language=Russian |date=25 July 2019}}</ref>

In September 2021, Miller made a surprise move to Iraq for [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]].

On 22 March 2023, [[Turan Tovuz]] announced the signing of Miller to a three-month contract, with the option of an additional year.<ref>{{cite web |title=Roderik Miller Molina “Turan Tovuz”da! |url=https://www.facebook.com/photo/?fbid=659575089507609&set=a.491494949648958 |website=facebook.com/TuranTovuzPFK/ |publisher=Turan Tovuz Facebook |access-date=22 March 2023 |language=Azerbaijani |date=22 March 2023}}</ref>

==International career==
Miller was part of the [[Panama national under-20 football team|Panama U-20]] squad  that played at the [[2011 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in [[Colombia]].<ref>{{FIFA player|344582}}</ref>

He made his senior debut for [[Panama national football team|Panama]] in an October 2011 [[FIFA World Cup qualification]] match against [[Dominica national football team|Dominica]] and has, as of 10 June 2015, earned a total of 10 caps, scoring no goals including a 2012 unofficial match against [[Guyana national football team|Guyana]]. He represented his country at the [[2013 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>[http://www.fepafut.com/noticias_detail.asp?id=3377 Julio Dely da listado de 23 jugadores para Copa Oro] - FEPAFUT {{in lang|es}}</ref>

